В В В В В В В В Admiring Nature in her wildest grace,
В В В В В В В В These northern scenes with weary feet I trace;
В В В В В В В В O'er many a winding dale and painful steep,
В В В В В В В В Th' abodes of covey'd grouse and timid sheep,
В В В В В В В В My savage journey, curious I pursue,
В В В В В В В В 'Till fam'd Breadalbane opens to my view.
В В В В В В В В The meeting cliffs each deep-sunk glen divides,
В В В В В В В В The woods, wild scatter'd, clothe their ample sides;
В В В В В В В В Th' outstretching lake, embosom'd 'mong the hills,
В В В В В В В В The eye with wonder and amazement fills;
В В В В В В В В The Tay, meand'ring sweet in infant pride,
В В В В В В В В The palace, rising on its verdant side;
В В В В В В В В The lawns, wood-fring'd in Nature's native taste;
В В В В В В В В The hillocks, dropt in Nature's careless haste;
В В В В В В В В The arches, striding o'er the new-born stream;
В В В В В В В В The village, glittering in the noontide beam.

В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *

В В В В В В В В Poetic ardours in my bosom swell,
В В В В В В В В Lone wand'ring by the hermit's mossy cell:
В В В В В В В В The sweeping theatre of hanging woods;
В В В В В В В В Th' incessant roar of headlong tumbling floods.

В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *В В В В В В В В В В В В  *

В В В В В В В В Here Poesy might wake her heav'n-taught lyre,
В В В В В В В В And look through Nature with creative fire;
В В В В В В В В Here, to the wrongs of fate half reconcil'd,
В В В В В В В В Misfortune's lighten'd steps might wander wild;
В В В В В В В В And Disappointment, in these lonely bounds,
В В В В В В В В Find balm to soothe her bitter, rankling wounds:
В В В В В В В В Here heart-struck Grief might heav'nward stretch her scan,
В В В В В В В В And injur'd Worth forget and pardon man.

